{
  "info": {
    "name": "API Doc & Demo Portal — Onboarding Collections",
    "description": "## Welcome to the API Demo Portal\n\nThis collection is your fastest path from zero to working API calls. Fork it, plug in your credentials, and run the **Core Features** flow end-to-end in under 5 minutes.\n\n---\n\n## How to Use This Collection\n\n### Step 1 — Fork & Configure\n1. Click **Fork** (top right in Postman)\n2. Select the `API Demo Portal — Sandbox` environment\n3. Set your `api_key` variable (get one free at `{{docs_url}}/signup`)\n\n### Step 2 — Run the Onboarding Flow\nOpen the **Runner**, select this collection, and run the `0 — Onboarding Flow` folder in order. Each request auto-saves IDs to collection variables so subsequent calls just work.\n\n### Step 3 — Explore Core Features\nEach top-level folder maps to a product area. The `★ Core Feature` tag marks the 20% of endpoints that cover 80% of use cases — start there.\n\n---\n\n## Key Variables\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `base_url` | API base URL (set per environment) |\n| `api_key` | Your API key |\n| `resource_id` | Auto-set by the Onboarding Flow |\n\n---\n\n## Environments\n- **Sandbox** — safe playground, data resets every 24h, no real charges\n- **Production** — live environment, requires paid plan\n\n## Support\nStuck? Open a ticket at `{{support_url}}` or ping us on Discord.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "api-doc-demo-portal-v1"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      { "key": "key",   "value": "Authorization",      "type": "string" },
      { "key": "value", "value": "Bearer {{api_key}}", "type": "string" },
      { "key": "in",    "value": "header",              "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",     "value": "{{base_url}}" },
    { "key": "resource_id",  "value": "" },
    { "key": "workspace_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "webhook_id",   "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0 — Onboarding Flow ⚡ (Start Here)",
      "description": "Run this folder end-to-end to onboard in < 5 minutes. Each request auto-saves response values so the next request just works — no copy-pasting IDs.\n\n**Expected run time:** ~2 minutes\n**What you'll do:** Verify auth → Create your first resource → Send your first event → Verify it was received",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Step 1 — Verify Auth",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Auth is valid — status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Response has user info', () => pm.expect(body.user).to.be.an('object'));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('workspace_id', body.user.default_workspace_id);",
                  "console.log('✅ Authenticated as:', body.user.email);",
                  "console.log('✅ Workspace:', body.user.default_workspace_id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["me"] }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — Authenticated",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": \"usr_abc123\",\n    \"email\": \"you@example.com\",\n    \"name\": \"Your Name\",\n    \"plan\": \"sandbox\",\n    \"default_workspace_id\": \"ws_xyz789\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-04-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"invalid_api_key\",\n  \"message\": \"The provided API key is invalid or has been revoked.\",\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.example.com/authentication\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 2 — Create Your First Resource ★",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Resource created — status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Resource has ID', () => pm.expect(body.id).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('resource_id', body.id);",
                  "console.log('✅ Created resource:', body.id);",
                  "console.log('   → resource_id saved to collection variables');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"My First Resource\",\n  \"description\": \"Created via the API Demo Portal onboarding flow\",\n  \"workspace_id\": \"{{workspace_id}}\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"mode\": \"sandbox\",\n    \"auto_process\": true\n  }\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"res_demo001\",\n  \"name\": \"My First Resource\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"workspace_id\": \"ws_xyz789\",\n  \"config\": { \"mode\": \"sandbox\", \"auto_process\": true },\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-02T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"_links\": {\n    \"self\": \"/resources/res_demo001\",\n    \"events\": \"/resources/res_demo001/events\",\n    \"docs\": \"https://docs.example.com/resources\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 3 — Send Your First Event ★",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Event accepted — status 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Event has ID', () => pm.expect(body.event_id).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('event_id', body.event_id);",
                  "console.log('✅ Event queued:', body.event_id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources/{{resource_id}}/events",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resources", "{{resource_id}}", "events"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"user.signup\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"user_id\": \"usr_demo_new\",\n    \"email\": \"newuser@example.com\",\n    \"source\": \"api_demo\"\n  },\n  \"idempotency_key\": \"onboarding-demo-event-001\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "202 Accepted",
              "status": "Accepted",
              "code": 202,
              "body": "{\n  \"event_id\": \"evt_abc999\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"resource_id\": \"res_demo001\",\n  \"estimated_processing_ms\": 150\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 4 — Verify Event Processed ★",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Event is processed or queued', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(['processed', 'queued']).to.include(body.status);",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('✅ Event status:', body.status);",
                  "if (body.status === 'processed') {",
                  "  console.log('🎉 Onboarding complete! Your first event was processed successfully.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/events/{{event_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["events", "{{event_id}}"]
            }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — Processed",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"evt_abc999\",\n  \"type\": \"user.signup\",\n  \"status\": \"processed\",\n  \"resource_id\": \"res_demo001\",\n  \"processed_at\": \"2026-04-02T10:00:00.150Z\",\n  \"result\": { \"triggered_workflows\": 2, \"notifications_sent\": 1 }\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1 — Authentication",
      "description": "API key management, token rotation, and OAuth flows.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Current User ★",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["me"] }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List API Keys",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api-keys", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api-keys"] }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create API Key",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api-keys", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api-keys"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"CI/CD pipeline key\",\n  \"scopes\": [\"resources:read\", \"events:write\"],\n  \"expires_at\": \"2027-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"key_new001\",\n  \"name\": \"CI/CD pipeline key\",\n  \"key\": \"sk_live_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX\",\n  \"scopes\": [\"resources:read\", \"events:write\"],\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-02T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"expires_at\": \"2027-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"_note\": \"Save this key — it will not be shown again.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Rotate API Key",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api-keys/{{key_id}}/rotate", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api-keys", "{{key_id}}", "rotate"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{ \"invalidate_old_after_seconds\": 300 }" }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke API Key",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api-keys/{{key_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api-keys", "{{key_id}}"] }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 — Resources (Core Feature) ★",
      "description": "Full CRUD for your primary resource type. **This is the most important folder** — all other product areas build on resources.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Resources ★",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources?workspace_id={{workspace_id}}&status=active&page=1&per_page=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resources"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "workspace_id", "value": "{{workspace_id}}" },
                { "key": "status",       "value": "active" },
                { "key": "page",         "value": "1" },
                { "key": "per_page",     "value": "20" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Resource ★",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Production Resource\",\n  \"workspace_id\": \"{{workspace_id}}\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"mode\": \"production\",\n    \"auto_process\": true,\n    \"retry_policy\": { \"max_attempts\": 3, \"backoff\": \"exponential\" }\n  },\n  \"tags\": { \"team\": \"backend\", \"env\": \"prod\" }\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Resource ★",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources/{{resource_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources", "{{resource_id}}"] }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Resource",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources/{{resource_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources", "{{resource_id}}"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Updated Resource Name\",\n  \"config\": { \"auto_process\": false }\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Resource",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources/{{resource_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources", "{{resource_id}}"] }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 — Events (Core Feature) ★",
      "description": "Send, query, and replay events. The event system is the backbone of all async workflows.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Send Event ★",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",    "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{$randomUUID}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources/{{resource_id}}/events", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources", "{{resource_id}}", "events"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"order.completed\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"order_id\": \"ord_12345\",\n    \"amount\": 9900,\n    \"currency\": \"usd\",\n    \"customer_id\": \"cus_abc\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Send Batch Events",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/events/batch", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["events", "batch"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"resource_id\": \"{{resource_id}}\",\n  \"events\": [\n    { \"type\": \"page.view\", \"payload\": { \"page\": \"/home\", \"user_id\": \"usr_1\" } },\n    { \"type\": \"page.view\", \"payload\": { \"page\": \"/pricing\", \"user_id\": \"usr_2\" } },\n    { \"type\": \"button.click\", \"payload\": { \"button\": \"cta_signup\", \"user_id\": \"usr_2\" } }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List Events",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources/{{resource_id}}/events?type=order.completed&from=2026-04-01&to=2026-04-02&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resources", "{{resource_id}}", "events"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "type",  "value": "order.completed" },
                { "key": "from",  "value": "2026-04-01" },
                { "key": "to",    "value": "2026-04-02" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Replay Event",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/events/{{event_id}}/replay", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["events", "{{event_id}}", "replay"] }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4 — Webhooks",
      "description": "Register, test, and manage webhook endpoints. Webhooks deliver events to your server in real time.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register Webhook ★",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('webhook_id', pm.response.json().id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/webhooks", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["webhooks"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"url\": \"https://your-server.example.com/webhooks/receiver\",\n  \"events\": [\"order.completed\", \"order.refunded\", \"user.signup\"],\n  \"secret\": \"whsec_your_signing_secret\",\n  \"description\": \"Production order webhook\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test Webhook",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/webhooks/{{webhook_id}}/test", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["webhooks", "{{webhook_id}}", "test"] }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"delivery_id\": \"dlv_test_001\",\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"http_status\": 200,\n  \"response_time_ms\": 143,\n  \"endpoint_url\": \"https://your-server.example.com/webhooks/receiver\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List Webhook Deliveries",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/webhooks/{{webhook_id}}/deliveries?status=failed&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["webhooks", "{{webhook_id}}", "deliveries"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "failed" },
                { "key": "limit",  "value": "20" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Retry Failed Delivery",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/webhooks/deliveries/{{delivery_id}}/retry", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["webhooks", "deliveries", "{{delivery_id}}", "retry"] }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Webhook",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/webhooks/{{webhook_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["webhooks", "{{webhook_id}}"] }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5 — Pagination & Filtering Patterns",
      "description": "Reference examples for all supported query patterns. Fork these as starting points for your integration.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Cursor Pagination",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources?limit=20&cursor={{next_cursor}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resources"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit",  "value": "20" },
                { "key": "cursor", "value": "{{next_cursor}}", "description": "Value of next_cursor from previous response" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — Paginated",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"data\": [ { \"id\": \"res_page2_001\" } ],\n  \"pagination\": {\n    \"has_more\": true,\n    \"next_cursor\": \"cur_eyJpZCI6InJlc19wYWdlM18wMDEifQ\",\n    \"total_count\": 347\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Filter by Tags",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources?tags[team]=backend&tags[env]=prod",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resources"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "tags[team]", "value": "backend" },
                { "key": "tags[env]",  "value": "prod" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Date Range Filter",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources?created_after=2026-03-01T00:00:00Z&created_before=2026-04-01T00:00:00Z",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["resources"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "created_after",  "value": "2026-03-01T00:00:00Z" },
                { "key": "created_before", "value": "2026-04-01T00:00:00Z" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6 — Error Reference",
      "description": "Documented error scenarios with example responses. Use these to test your error handling before going to production.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "401 — Invalid API Key",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer sk_invalid_key_example" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["me"] }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"invalid_api_key\",\n  \"message\": \"The provided API key is invalid or revoked.\",\n  \"request_id\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.example.com/errors#invalid_api_key\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "422 — Validation Error",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{ \"config\": {} }" }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "422 Unprocessable Entity",
              "status": "Unprocessable Entity",
              "code": 422,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"validation_error\",\n  \"message\": \"Request body validation failed.\",\n  \"fields\": {\n    \"name\": [\"required\"],\n    \"workspace_id\": [\"required\"]\n  },\n  \"request_id\": \"req_def456\",\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.example.com/errors#validation_error\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "429 — Rate Limited",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/resources", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["resources"] }
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "429 Too Many Requests",
              "status": "Too Many Requests",
              "code": 429,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Retry-After",         "value": "30" },
                { "key": "X-RateLimit-Limit",   "value": "1000" },
                { "key": "X-RateLimit-Reset",   "value": "1743591600" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\",\n  \"message\": \"You have exceeded 1000 requests per minute. Retry after 30 seconds.\",\n  \"retry_after\": 30,\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.example.com/rate-limiting\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
